         https://github.com/inboxpraveen/Py-Internals
         Licensed under the PI Community License"

   b) The attribution must be:
      - Visible to end users (not hidden in comments or build artifacts)
      - Reasonably prominent (e.g., in a footer, credits page, or About section)
      - Linked to the original project URL where technically feasible

   c) If you have modified the materials, you must indicate that changes
      were made and must not imply that the original author endorses your
      modified version.

B. SHARE-ALIKE (For derivatives)

   If you remix, transform, or build upon the material to create a derivative
   educational course or component library, you must distribute your
   contributions under the same license (PI Community License v1.0 or later)
   or a compatible open license.

   This ensures the educational commons remains open for everyone.

C. NON-COMMERCIAL (For commercial use, see below)

   The materials may NOT be used for direct commercial gain without explicit
